THE RISK (context, do not rewrite): perturbation [{"nodeId":"serviceableFactor","op":"set","value":0.35,"note":"Year-1 realistic footprint: DE+NL via one distributor plus partial direct coverage; CH and CEE tail unbuilt"}], likelihood 0.55, category model-structure

FIELDS TO REWRITE:
{
 "title": "serviceableFactor 0.55 is a stock; a pre-launch entrant only owns a flow — Year-1 reach is realistically two countries, one channel",
 "narrative": "The 0.55 serviceable share treats channel and regulatory reach as an endowment. But reach is BUILT during the same 12 months it is supposed to be harvested: distributor contracts signed, country registrations obtained, support commitments staffed, five languages covered. The only quantified external analogues the research found for a realistically serviceable slice are 12% (Scalarly's regional-narrowing example) and single-digit SOM ranges — nothing supports 45–65% for a pre-launch vendor. Concretely: Switzerland (8% of TAM) is non-EU and needs its own conformity path; Poland and 'Other CE' need local-language channel that doesn't exist yet; even in Germany, coverage means signed distributors, not the country's existence. A pre-launch Year-1 footprint of DE plus NL through one distributor is closer to 0.30–0.35 of TAM than 0.55.",
 "mechanism": [
  {
   "step": "trigger",
   "text": "The 0.55 is an unanchored assumption leaf: every external quantified analogue found sits far lower (12% regional-narrowing example; investor preference for bottom-up over top-down reach claims), and no bottom-up channel-coverage model exists in the ledger",
   "refs": [
    "digest:serviceable-benchmark#c3",
    "digest:serviceable-benchmark#c13",
    "ledger:serviceableFactor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "propagation",
   "text": "Reach must be constructed country-by-country inside the Year-1 window: SAM is a capability statement (compliance, integrations, support model, channel) and each element is unbuilt at launch; non-EU Switzerland (8% of the geo split) and the CEE tail require separate conformity and channel work",
   "refs": [
    "digest:serviceable-benchmark#c12",
    "digest:serviceable-benchmark#c10",
    "ledger:geo.CH",
    "ledger:geo.other"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "model-impact",
   "text": "Year-1 serviceable share falls from 0.55 toward a two-country, one-channel footprint; SAM contracts proportionally and YAM with it, even if the obtainable percentage of that SAM holds",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:serviceableFactor",
    "ledger:geo.DE"
   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "The 0.55 carries a wide, symmetric band (0.45–0.65) that looks like honest uncertainty about a level. What's hidden is that for a pre-launch venture the true Year-1 value starts near zero and ramps — the band brackets the steady state, not the first year, and the funnel's lack of a time axis makes the two indistinguishable.",
 "falsifier": "Signed distribution or direct-coverage agreements plus completed country registrations covering ≥55% of the CE-7 TAM base (by geo weight) within the first quarter after launch.",
 "likelihoodRationale": "Judgment anchored on the digests' finding that no external evidence supports 45–65% reach for any comparable vendor and that reach components (certs, channel, support) verifiably do not exist pre-launch; offset by the possibility of a single pan-CE master distributor deal covering multiple countries at once. [evidence revision: Evidence modestly strengthens the hypothesis: independent sizing guides confirm SOM is capacity-built not a top-down SAM fraction, and observed real-world distributor deals are single-country/exclusive and pre-revenue, consistent with a narrow two-country Year-1 footprint. No source demonstrated any pre-launch vendor achieving ≥55% multi-country coverage in the first quarter (falsifier unmet). The residual uncertainty—a single pan-regional master distributor could compress the timeline—keeps this from moving higher.]"
}

